description.plain:
Lauren Ashley Daigle (born September 9, 1991) is an American singer from Lafayette, Louisiana. Since signing with Centricity Music, Daigle has made herself well known in the music industry by working with artists such as Reba McEntire, Switchfoot, NEEDTOBREATHE, and performing on the Blade Runner 2049 Soundtrack.
She is also a current member of The Belonging Co, CentricWorship, and is former member of North Point InsideOut.

songs.title: You Say

description.plain:
It was the day after my very first Award show, and I remember being completely overwhelmed. I walked into the studio with my producers, Paul and Jason, and they asked “What’s going on in your world? How has it been?”, it was the first time we had written since “How Can It Be.” I was feeling overwhelmed that much had happened the night before. How do I come back down to normal? How do I come back down to reality?

This brought up the issue of identity and trying to figure out how to exist when I feel like so many things were pulling me in so many different directions. We pretty quickly finished the writing and demo recording that day.

Over the course of two years of touring, I would sing “You Say” every night.  I remember starting to hear fans sing along to a song that had never been heard before. When it came time to make the record, it was a really fun process to have the challenge presented with something that I felt like I’d been living with. I felt like I got to a place of expressing this song exactly how I wanted to sing it.

songs.title: Rescue

description.plain: “Rescue” by Lauren Daigle envelopes the aspect of God’s willingness to go to great lengths to rescue Lauren, even when no one else can hear her. Rescue is supposed to be sung from God’s perspective.

songs.title: Look Up Child

description.plain: This song is like a prayer. The person is asking God where he is, and he is saying look up. He  said to look up, because he is showing the person he is there and in heaven, watching and guiding the person’s soul. The person replies, saying that he/she understands, and knows that God will protect the person, like he did the world as his son, on the cross.
